So the stealth racer&nbsp;slows going into and through the turns, and he accelerates coming off the turns and through the straightaways.<div>His gentle surging&nbsp;and slowing disrupts his pursuers&nbsp;from any&nbsp;easy&nbsp;passing attempts.</div><div>Passing HIM is going to have a steep cost.</div><div>Extra&nbsp;acceleration is needed&nbsp;to complete a&nbsp;pass, and EXTRA slowing (even&nbsp;braking) may be needed if running a&nbsp;wide turn is to be avoided by the pursuer.</div>